    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 5 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER ES65-5 - DISASSEMBLE - CASE
        AND GEARS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="17">
        <title>CASE AND GEARS</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1301304">Figure 4</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1301304" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1301304" filename="../figg13/G1301304.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 4. Case and Gears</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. MAINSHAFT REAR BEARING CAP</callout1>
                <callout1>2. SEAL</callout1>
                <callout1>3. LIFT HOOK</callout1>
                <callout1>4. COUNTERSHAFT REAR BEARING CAP</callout1>
                <callout1>5. GASKET</callout1>
                <callout1>6. FILL PLUG</callout1>
                <callout1>7. DRAIN PLUG</callout1>
                <callout1>8. COUNTERSHAFT FRONT BEARING CAP</callout1>
                <callout1>9. 6 BOLT PTO COVER</callout1>
                <callout1>10. TRANSMISSION COVER</callout1>
                <callout1>11. CLUTCH HOUSING GASKET</callout1>
                <callout1>12. INSPECTION PLATE</callout1>
                <callout1>13. LOCKSTRAP</callout1>
                <callout1>14. CLUTCH HOUSING</callout1>
                <callout1>15. FRONT BEARING CAP</callout1>
                <callout1>16. 8 BOLT PTO COVER</callout1>
                <callout1>17. BRAKE STUD</callout1>
                <callout1>18. BRAKE STUD PIN</callout1>
                <callout1>19. PLUG</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the bolts that retain the shifter housing to the transmission case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301305">Figure 5</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301305" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301305" filename="../figg13/G1301305.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 5. Remove Bolts Retaining Shift Housing to Transmission Case</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lift the shifter housing up and off the transmission case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301306">Figure 6</hotlnk>).
                <emph type="bold"></emph>
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301306" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301306" filename="../figg13/G1301306.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 6. Lift Shifter Housing Up and Off Transmission Case</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Be careful not to lose the three poppet balls and springs from the top of the shifter
                        housing.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To prevent the gears from rotating, lock the transmission in two gears (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301307">Figure 7</hotlnk>). For example, engage 2nd-3rd speed synchronizer with the
                2nd-3rd speed gear and 4th-5th speed synchronizer with the 4th-5th speed gear. Use pry bars to shift the
                synchronizers into gear.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301307" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301307" filename="../figg13/G1301307.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 7. Lock Transmission in Two Gears</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the nut, washer and end yoke/flange (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301308">Figure 8</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301308" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301308" filename="../figg13/G1301308.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 8. Remove Nut, Washer, and End Yoke/Flange</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the rear bearing cap bolts and pry the cap away from the case with a pry bar (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301309">Figure 9</hotlnk>). Remove the gasket from the case and bearing cap.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301309" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301309" filename="../figg13/G1301309.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 9. Pry Cap Away From Case</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the bearing cup and oil seal for wear or damage (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301310">Figure 10</hotlnk>). Tap them out with a drift or punch if replacement is
                required.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301310" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301310" filename="../figg13/G1301310.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 10. Inspect Bearing Cup and Oil Seal</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the speedometer gear from the mainshaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301311">Figure 11</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301311" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301311" filename="../figg13/G1301311.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 11. Remove Speedometer Gear From Mainshaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the bolts from the front bearing cap. Remove the bearing cap and gasket (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301312">Figure 12</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301312" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301312" filename="../figg13/G1301312.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 12. Remove Bearing Cap and Gasket</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the bearing cup and oil seal. Replace the seal and bearing cup if worn or damaged (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301313">Figure 13</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301313" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301313" filename="../figg13/G1301313.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 13. Inspect Bearing Cup and Oil Seal</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the input shaft from the front of the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301314">Figure 14</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301314" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301314" filename="../figg13/G1301314.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 14. Remove Input Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lift the mainshaft assembly out of the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301315">Figure 15</hotlnk>). The easiest method is with a hoist and hook around the
                2nd-3rd speed synchronizer blocker pins. Exercise care not to damage the bearings against the case.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301315" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301315" filename="../figg13/G1301315.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 15. Lift Mainshaft Assembly Out of Case</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the countershaft rear bearing cap and gasket (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301316">Figure 16</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301316" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301316" filename="../figg13/G1301316.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 16. Remove Countershaft Rear Bearing Cap and Gasket</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The countershaft may be moved rearward, causing the bearing cup to fall out of the case bore
                        and exposing the rear bearing. Use caution not to damage or brinell the bearing or bearing cup.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the reverse idler shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301317">Figure 17</hotlnk>). Puller ZTSE-4324 is recommended. Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s13013_35.xml" xrefid="hl1301301">SPECIAL TOOLS
                    <xref refid="hl1301301"/>
                </hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301317" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301317" filename="../figg13/G1301317.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 17. Remove Reverse Idler Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide the idler shaft out of the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301318">Figure 18</hotlnk>). Then remove the two thrust washers, reverse idler gear,
                two caged pocket bearings, and spacer (between caged bearings).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301318" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301318" filename="../figg13/G1301318.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 18. Slide Idler Shaft Out of Case</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tie a rope or sling around the countershaft (behind the countershaft drive gear) and lift
                the countershaft assembly out of the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301319">Figure 19</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301319" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301319" filename="../figg13/G1301319.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 19. Lift Countershaft Assembly Out of Case</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the clutch housing and gasket (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301320">Figure 20</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301320" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301320" filename="../figg13/G1301320.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 20. Remove Clutch Housing and Gasket</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
